Maintenance Shutdowns: The Himachal Pradesh State Electricity Board (HPSEB) frequently schedules maintenance on major feeders, such as the 132 KV sub-station in Tahliwal or Bangana, which can lead to outages lasting between 4 to 8 hours.
Rural vs. Urban: Rural areas in Himachal Pradesh historically experience significantly more power cut hours (averaging over 2,500 hours annually in some years) compared to urban centers like Una city, where infrastructure is more redundant.
Seasonal Fluctuations: Power demand spikes during peak agricultural seasons (like paddy sowing) can lead to unscheduled cuts as power is diverted to the farming sector. 
Impact on Internet Connection
Infrastructure Resilience: Most internet service providers (ISPs) like Airtel Xstream Fiber, JioFiber, and BSNL have backup generators or batteries at their main hubs. This means the internet signal often remains active in the lines even if your house loses power.
Home Equipment Failure: Your internet will drop primarily because your modem and router shut down without electricity.
Cellular Congestion: During widespread outages, local mobile towers may become congested as more people switch to mobile data, leading to slower speeds even if your phone remains powered. 
Recommended Solutions for Your Brand Goal
For a "farm-to-product" brand where consistent connectivity is needed for orders and operations, consider these backup options:
Router UPS: A dedicated mini-UPS (like those from Energy Intelligence or APC) can keep your Wi-Fi running for 4 to 10 hours.
Dual Connection: Use a fiber connection (like Airtel or Jio) as your primary and a BSNL or Vi data card/hotspot as a backup, as different towers may have different backup capacities.
