How to Collect the Soil Sample (The "V-Cut" Method)
Correct sampling is critical. Since you don't own the land yet, ask the current owner for permission to take samples from 4-5 random spots. 
Clear the Surface: Scrape off grass and litter from the surface.
Dig a V-Shape: Dig a V-shaped pit 6–8 inches deep (for crops) or 1 foot deep (for fruit trees).
Slice the Soil: Take a 1-inch thick slice of soil from top to bottom along one side of the "V".
Mix & Pack: Collect samples from 5-8 spots, mix them thoroughly in a clean bucket (no chemical residue), and keep about 500g.
Label: Put it in a clean cloth or plastic bag. Label it with:
